{"lemma":"أَبْطَحانِ","slug":"أَبْطَحانِ","root":"ب.ط.ح","root_slug":"ب-ط-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ط-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n2744"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"level, flat, even"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ب ط ح (b ṭ ḥ)."},"ipa":["/ʔab.tˤaħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2744","headword_ar":"اَبْطَحُ","root":"bTH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally an epithet [and therefore imperfectly decl.], (M, TA,) that is, an epithet converted into a subst., and not used as an epithet, (Ham p. 21,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wide water-course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channel of a torrent, in which are fine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken, pebbles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K, and Ham ubi suprà;) so called because the water goes in it to the right and left; [i. e. spreads widely; see 7;] (AA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baToHaA='u","text_ar":"بَطْحَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K, Ham,) fem. of the former, and, like it, an epithet converted into a subst.; (Ham ubi suprà;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTiyHapN","text_ar":"بَطِيحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTiHN","text_ar":"بَطِحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a water-course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channel of a torrent, in which are sand and pebbles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baToHaA='u","text_ar":"بَطْحَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) or a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide place"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a water-course"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTHp","text_ar":"بطحة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baToHapN","text_ar":"بَطْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is explained by Freytag, but without his stating on what authority, as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a depressed place through which water flows, abounding with pebbles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biToHapN","text_ar":"بِطْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in like manner Golius explains the former, but mentions the latter as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTyHp","text_ar":"بطيحة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) or, accord. to AHn, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bottom of a water-course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channel of a torrent, producing no plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baToHaA='u","text_ar":"بَطْحَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as has been drawn along by the torrents:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft pebbles in the bottom of the water-course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channel of a torrent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboTaHu","text_ar":"اَبْطَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAth, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft earth, such as has been drawn along by the torrents, in the bottom of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taloEap","text_ar":"تَلْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a water-course"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a valley;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboTaH","text_ar":"اَبْطَح"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baToHaA='","text_ar":"بَطْحَا=ء","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley are its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth and soft pebbles:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, TA:) and accord. to AA, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTiHN","text_ar":"بَطِحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sand in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baToHaA='","text_ar":"بَطْحَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaATiHu","text_ar":"اَبَاطِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biTaAHN","text_ar":"بِطَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTaAy^iHu","text_ar":"بَطَايِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) the first of these, and the second also, contr. to analogy, being pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbTH","text_ar":"ابطح"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or both are pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTHA='","text_ar":"بطحا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", contr. to analogy; (Ham p. 251;) or the first is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbTH","text_ar":"ابطح"},{"kind":"text","text":", formed after the manner of the pl. of a subst. of this measure, though the sing. is originally an epithet; (M, TA;) and the second, as is asserted by more than one, is correctly pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTHA='","text_ar":"بطحا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baToHaAwaAtN","text_ar":"بَطْحَاوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and the third is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTyHp","text_ar":"بطيحة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","S","A","K","Ham","Mgh","Msb","ISd","IAth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}